race.comment: Former NSW galloper MIND OVER MATTER (2) is having his first run for the new stable but should find this assignment easier than what he faced down south. Gets the services of Butler in the irons to navigate from the sticky alley and will be right there when the whips are cracking. The well-related PONTIUS (5) (half to Listed winner Westport) is facing the starter for the first time but has shown ability at the trials and won't need to be a superstar to be competitive against this lot. Worth keeping very safe. MISS KIYOSHI (12) is another on debut and is sure to be well-educated out of the McGuire yard. Monitor market moves. PENROD (4) was a touch disappointing last time out but go on the solid third at the Sunny Coast two back. Worth another chance. SECRET SCOUT (6) best of the rest in a race with a long tail.
